description: The Punjab government has suspended seven police officers for negligence after gangster Lawrence Bishnoi conducted an interview from custody. The interview took place via video-conferencing while Bishnoi was in the custody of the CIA in Kharar, Mohali district. A Special Investigation Team led by special DGP Prabodh Kumar identified these officers' failures.

description: Eight men, aged 19-21, were arrested for the brutal gang rape of a 19-year-old newlywed bride at a picnic spot in Rewa, Madhya Pradesh. The assailants encountered the couple during their visit to Bhairav Baba temple, subsequently attacking them and filming the assault. Police have charged all involved, and court proceedings have begun.

description: Gujarati is the third most-spoken language among Indian immigrants in Canada, with a notable increase between 2016 and 2021. Immigration consultant highlights the shift towards Canada due to visa issues with the US, UK, Australia, and New Zealand, though recent policy changes pose challenges.

description: The govt plans a special joint Parliament sitting on Nov 26 to mark the 75th anniversary of the Constitution's adoption. description: Ankalu Dasru Tulavi, a notorious Maoist with 226 cases, including 54 killings, was killed in a siege of the Maoist headquarters in Abujmarh on Oct 21. Tulavi, a key figure in the Maoist supply chain, resisted surrender for 33 years before being neutralized.

description: Cricketer Mahendra Singh Dhoni collaborates with the Election Commission to boost voter awareness during Jharkhand's assembly polls. The child expressed happiness living with them and wished for her mother to join. The mother claimed her husband is unfit to care due to addiction and alleged harassment by in-laws.

description: ED conducted raids in multiple cities over alleged black-marketing and fake ticket sales for Coldplay and Diljit Dosanjh concerts. While we and our franchisees don’t have records for all positions dating back to the early ’80s, what makes ‘1 in 8’ so powerful is the shared experience so many Americans have had."

title: MS Dhoni breaks silence on 'Thala for a reason' memes

description: Pop icon Beyoncé supported Kamala Harris at a Houston rally, focusing on abortion rights, voter importance, and her vision for a united world. Beyoncé, accompanied by Kelly Rowland, endorsed Harris, who uses her song 'Freedom' as a campaign anthem, highlighting Texas' strict abortion laws and the urgency of voting.
title: 'I'm here as a mother': Beyoncé backs Kamala Harris for President

description: India struggled on the second day of the second Test against New Zealand in Pune, ending their innings at 156, trailing by 103 runs. Mitchell Santner's impressive 7-53 and Tom Latham's crucial 86 were key highlights. India's batting faltered, putting their 18-home Test series winning streak at risk as New Zealand led by 301 runs.
title: India's home run of 18 consecutive series wins in danger of ending

description: On 26.10.24, individuals associated with various numerology numbers will encounter unique influences affecting their personal growth, decision-making, responsibilities, and emotional states. The day promises opportunities for reflection, optimism, overcoming obstacles, and embracing changes, while urging caution against impulsive actions, procrastination, or rigid thinking to achieve balance and harmonious outcomes in personal and professional spheres.
title: Numerology Predictions Today: Read your personalised forecast for no. 1 to 9

description: Microsoft has terminated two employees who organised an unauthorised vigil for Palestinians killed in Gaza, arguing it was to honour victims and highlight Microsoft's involvement in the conflict. The dismissed individuals, Abdelrahman Mohamed and Hossam Nasr, were part of 'No Azure for Apartheid.' The incident mirrors a similar situation at Google involving protests against its deal with the Israeli government.
title: Microsoft fires staff over Gaza vigil for Palestinians

description: Matthew Perry's mother, Suzanne Morrison, shares an emotional recollection of their last conversation, hinting he had a premonition about his fate. The beloved 'Friends' star passed away at 54 due to acute ketamine effects, leaving family, friends, and fans deeply mourning his loss.
title: What do Matthew Perry's final words hint at about his demise? Mother reveals

description: The BCCI announced an 18-member squad for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy series against Australia, introducing newcomers Harshit Rana and Nitish Kumar Reddy. Exclusions of notable players Kuldeep Yadav and Mohammed Shami are due to injuries. Fan outrage ensued over the exclusion of in-form batsman Ruturaj Gaikwad. Gaikwad is currently the leading run-scorer for Maharashtra in the ongoing Ranji Trophy tournament.
title: Ruturaj's omission from India squads sparks fan backlash
Was US informed ahead of Israel's strikes on Iran? White House responds

description: BCCI has announced an 18-member squad for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy against Australia starting November 22 in Perth. Newcomers Abhimanyu Easwaran, Harshit Rana, and Nitish Rana are included. Mohammed Shami is absent due to knee issues, while Kuldeep Yadav is out for groin treatment. Shami, however, on Sunday shared a video on his social media showcasing his bowling in the nets.​​
title: Why Shami missed out on India’s Test squad for BGT

description: Israel carried out air strikes in Iran on Saturday, leading to multiple powerful explosions in Tehran and Karaj. The cause remains unclear, and Iranian officials warn of stronger retaliation against any offensive action. Eyewitnesses reported loud sounds and a red sky. This follows a recent ballistic missile attack by Iran on Israel.
title: Israel conducts retaliatory strikes against Iran: Top developments

description: Environment minister Arun Kumar Saxena urged NCR residents to use public transport, carpool, and walk to reduce vehicular pollution in areas with weak metro connectivity. During a meeting on worsening AQI levels, displeasure was expressed over non-compliance with vehicular fitness guidelines. Chief Secretary Singh warned of prosecution for negligent officials, promoting EVs and CNG vehicles.
title: Why UP minister’s AQI advice changed from public transport to walking, carpool

description: Xiaomi's new electric vehicle, the SU7, has garnered unexpected praise from Ford CEO Jim Farley, who lauded its performance and technology. The sleek sedan competes strongly with Tesla, boasting a top speed of 62 mph in 2.7 seconds and a 435-mile range. Despite geopolitical challenges, Chinese brands like Xiaomi continue to influence the global EV market.
title: 'I don't like talking about competition, but ...': Ford CEO

description: Intel, the largest recipient of US CHIPS Act funds, faces financial woes, raising concerns for the Biden administration. Despite a $100 billion investment pledge and substantial government support, Intel's struggles with layoffs and project delays have alarmed officials. Commerce Secretary Gina Raimondo has urged tech leaders to prioritize US-made chips to revitalize the industry.
title: Why US' Raimondo told CEOs of other companies to buy chips from Intel

description: "The type of information on phones used by a presidential candidate and his running mate could be a gold mine for an intelligence agency: Who they called and texted, how often they communicated with certain people, and how long they talked to those people could be highly valuable to an adversary like China. That sort of communications data could be even more useful if hackers could observe it in real time," the NYT report said.
title: Chinese hackers targeted Trump, JD Vance's phones: Report

description: In Kanpur, Bajrang Dal members filed a complaint against a Muslim man named Mohd Kallu for wearing a 'Jai Shri Ram' t-shirt allegedly to conceal his identity and selling suspected adulterated 'veg kebabs' at a local eatery. Police are investigating the accusations after calming the agitated activists.
title: Bajrang Dal files plaint against Muslim man for selling ‘adulterated veg kebabs’

description: On the fourth day of Maharashtra assembly polls nominations, 991 candidates, including key figures, filed their papers. Deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis’s affidavits highlight a significant increase in income and assets over the past decade. Fadnavis and his wife Amruta's combined assets rose to Rs 13.27 crore, with notable investments in gold and the share market.
title: Fadnavis couple income soars over a decade, wife richer than deputy CM
